HEADWORD: Omphalomancy
<hw>Om"pha*lo*man"cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Omphalo-</ets> + <ets>-mancy</ets>.]</ety> <def>Divination by
means of a child's navel, to learn how many children the mother may
have.</def> <rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Omphalomesaraic</ent>⟦br⟧
